<a href="#0" id="0">A CI must engage in dialogue with its human partner.</a>
<a href="#1" id="1">As an ongoing example, consider a kitchen CI that is asked, “ How do you make soup? ” A CI with extensive knowledge must filter its possible responses, because its help will only be valued if it is neither too simplistic (e.g., “ Just open a can and heat the contents. ” ) nor too detailed (e.g., “ … the history of soup is probably as old as the history of cooking … ” {sup:6}).</a>
<a href="#2" id="2">A CI should also be able to explain its answers to its human collaborator.</a>
<a href="#3" id="3">A CI should also tailor itself to the needs of the person it serves.</a>
